 ;; ===== BEHAVIORAL NOTES =====
 ;; Critical quirks that affect how you use the Wing

 :quirks
 ["Muting a channel kills ALL signal including pre-fader sends. Use main/N/on=0 to remove from main instead."
  "FX slot can only be on one insert at a time. Assigning elsewhere silently removes it."
  "Channel display name comes from input source (/io/in/GRP/N/name), not /ch/N/name."
  "Names and colors must be set on the input source, not the channel strip."
  "Two channels on the same USB input: Wing silently drops signal on the second."
  "Stereo mode defaults to mono. Must explicitly set mode=ST."
  "Wing outputs reject CH group for high channel numbers. Use USR as intermediary."
  "Sidechain routing (/dynsc/src, /gatesc/src) can't be set via OSC/wapi. Use touchscreen."
  "Monitor section (/cfg/mon) can't be accessed via wapi. Use oscsend or touchscreen."
  "Matrix EQ uses numbered params (band 1: /eq/1-4, band 2: /eq/5-7, ..., band 8: /eq/23-26)."
  "Channel EQ uses named params (/eq/lg, /eq/lf, /eq/1g, /eq/hg, etc.)."]}
